Resolution: I added a constraint when resolving a call so that a message pops up informing the user that an Incident cannot be resolved while there is an outstanding loan. I then created a once off import of AD and changed the substring on Campus so that it could pull through DC/DCPS
Subject: Three things
Symptom:
Thanks for this am
 
1.	Please can you urgently make sure that no call can be resolved/closed if there is a loan outstanding? This was the case previously and something has changed.
2.	Our AD is now setup as we want it - how are you pulling this? I think that the cystom expression for campus in employer internal blueprint needs to pull one OU ‘less” from the end if you know what I mean? 
CN=Alison Cunnold,OU=Admin,OU=Staff,OU=DCPS,DC=DC-Domain,DC=dc,DC=wcape,DC=school,DC=za
CN=Will Steenkamp,OU=Academic,OU=Staff,OU=DC,DC=DC-Domain,DC=dc,DC=wcape,DC=school,DC=za
Campus needs to pull DCPS/DC as the campus and its pulling staff
 
I don’t think that AD is synchoronised actually as I had to manipulate the string to reflect what I can see in our AD; Can you please force a sync?
HTML_Description:
Thanks for this am

2.	Our AD is now setup as we want it - how are you pulling this? I think that the cystom expression for campus in employer internal blueprint needs to pull one OU ‘less” from the end if you know what I mean? 
CN=Alison Cunnold,OU=Admin,OU=Staff,OU=DCPS,DC=DC-Domain,DC=dc,DC=wcape,DC=school,DC=za
